caption: (Translated by Google) Very bad!!! Visit this place at 9am to buy a breakfast and it turned out that they are not open yet. In the hours indicated in gmaps it says that they are open and that they close at 12 at night. I come from Queens and when I arrived I see that they are not open yet ... They should edit the hours that they added in the gmaps information so that clients like me do not waste their time when they arrive and see the business closed ... Another thing, no I know why breakfasts are promoted on Instagram if they don't really open early or is it that they sell breakfasts at 12 o'clock in the morning? 🤔  I came back another day and apparently they moved the business closer to where it was before. They took my order quickly, although the waiting time is a bit long. I did not see it very busy when I went but I did notice that they had a lot of online orders waiting. Hopefully they are better organized and thus the waiting time is reduced .. besides my ta good there was another client waiting first than me ...  (Original) Muy mal!!! Vengo desde Queens y cuando llegó veo que no están abiertos aún.... Deberían editar el horario que agregaron en la información de gmaps para que clientes como yo no pierdan su tiempo al llegar y ver el negocio cerrado... Otra cosa, no se para que promocionan los desayunos por Instagram si en realidad no abren temprano o es acaso que venden los desayunos a las 12 de día?🤔  Regresé otro día y al parecer mudaron el negocio cerca de donde estaba antes. This place is a Gem in the high bridge area of the Bronx. This area is a true food desert! Although Emergency snack bar isn't serving up healthy food it does provide some variety and an alternative to Kennedy fried, johnnys fried and bodega sandwiches.  Emergency has an impressive selection of what I like to call 420 foods. The kind of things your looking for when you have the munchies. They have burgers, chicken salads, sandwiches and Latin treats like rellenas de papa and pastelitos to name a few. They also serve fresh fruit juice like papaya or pineapple. My fav thing to order here is the Dominican hot dog. This is a large hot dog loaded with ground beef, cheese and potato straws and topped with ketchup and mayo. The ultimate fat food! I enjoy every bite of this hotdog every time I get it. I usually get fries with it. Their fries aren't your standard bland crinkle cut fries a lot of places serve. The fries are battered, seasoned and crispy! This dish is my go to when I'm in this area and looking for a a high calorie treat. Their juices are also A1. The pinnacle is my favorite! It tastes like 100 percent pineapple and some artificially flavored drink loaded with HFCS.  4 stars for emergency. Food is great, prices are reasonable and they are open late! The service can be slow. At times I've found myself waiting 20+ mins for a simple order. To avoid this I would call in advance. Another thing to their credit is they accept debit cards with the ridiculously high min transaction amount business in the area have. They also deliver.
